				<td colspan="2"><span>yzyh, unless you have used it with low mana bar, you are guessing, just like me.  The difference is I'm basing my guess on known issues with bards and ways we get mana back, or more properly ways we do not get it back.
<br />

<br />
Necro mana dumps, if we get anything significant from it, I haven't been able to tell.
<br />
Mod Rods, if we get anything significant from it, I haven't been able to tell.
<br />
KEI and any mind/mana flow buff does not increase our mana regen at all.  We get the benefit from the int giving us a larger mana pool, but not a faster mana regen.
<br />
Bard Mana Songs do nothing for our mana regen.
<br />

<br />
To the best of my knowledge, the ONLY things that help us are worn mana regeneration items and augments, AA (mental clarity line) and Tribute, with a max worn/augment/tribute combination of 15mr.
<br />

<br />
With all that in mind, I feel it is a safe bet to say that the claws do not give us any mana, or if they do, it is so minor as to be a joke.
<br />

<br />
Now, if you are posting from personal, not secondhand, knowledge where you did it yourself, then please say so, and I will stand corrected.</span></td>
